Source: reprozip
Maintainer: Remi Rampin <remirampin@gmail.com>
Homepage: https://vida-nyu.github.io/reprozip/
Section: misc
Priority: optional
X-Python-Version: >= 2.7.3
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 9), dh-python, python-all, python-setuptools

Package: reprozip
Architecture: i386 amd64
Depends: ${python:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, python-rpaths (>= 0.8)
Recommends: reprounzip
Description: reproducible experiment packer
 ReproZip is a tool aimed at simplifying the process of creating reproducible
 experiments from command-line executions, a frequently-used common denominator
 in computational science. It tracks operating system calls and creates a
 package that contains all the binaries, files and dependencies required to run
 a given command on the author's computational environment (packing step). A
 reviewer can then extract the experiment in his environment to reproduce the
 results (unpacking step).
 .
 This package contains the reprozip program, responsible for the packing step.

Package: reprounzip
Architecture: all
Depends: ${python:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, python-rpaths (>= 0.8)
